  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (compound adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is documented for six of seven validation activities. The package is presented as accepted and superficially complete. Two latent defects are embedded: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom lineage (W-EP-01, Critical), and one validation result omits hasUncertaintyQuantification entirely (W-AL-01, High), together satisfying the COMPOUND-01 trigger condition.",
