      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) prediction vs. in-vitro measurement",
      "description": "Predicted NIH values from the power-law hemolysis model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories are compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements at all five operating points. Predicted NIH falls within 18% of measured values at four of five points; the fifth point (highest shear, 6000 RPM) shows a 27% over-prediction consistent with known model-form limitations at extreme shear rates. The assessment team accepted this discrepancy given the conservative (over-predicting) direction relative to the clinical threshold. This validation result does not carry a formal uncertainty quantification record; the team relied on the deterministic power-law sensitivity sweep documented separately in the design file rather than a probabilistic UQ activity."
